6:
Argh... How the heck do I go about
this?
10:
Hey, Karina? You sounded pretty
upset a moment ago...
14: Are you in a slump again?
18:
...No, quite the opposite... And that's
where the trouble's coming from!
21:
This world's just so overwhelming!
It's full of designs and methods I'd
never see back home!
25:
And it all just looks so GREAT! I'm
getting so many new ideas my brain
can hardly take it!
29:
Sounds like you're determined to
make the most of it... I'm glad to
hear you're making progress.
32:
Thanks, Alk! I really am! And that's
why I'm thinking of going to this!
36:
"Palpebra New Designer Contest"...
Huh! You're going to join a contest?
40:
Yeah! It's time for me to show
everyone all the progress I've made
in this new world!
45:
There are lots of designs here. This
kimono here... Wait. Is this a dress?
49:
I haven't really decided yet, but I
want to put all of my skills into the
design!
52:
Using the materials of a kimono, the
form of an android... And the hottest
fashion from back home, too! I want
to put it all together!
57:
Maybe that's going a little
overboard?
61:
I'm entering to win, so I've gotta give
it everything I've got!
64:
Back when my mom was my age,
she was winning awards left and
right!
66: I know I can do it too... I HAVE to!
70:
Guess you'll need fabric and other
materials to make clothes. How
much do you think you'll need?
74: D-do you want to help me?
84:
Th-thank you!
Um... I guess the first thing I'll need isâ€”
94: Ta-da! The contest results are here!
102:
I haven't looked yet, I'm too nervous!
I wanted to look at it together!
120:
Oh! But it looks like the judges left
comments for the top-performing
contestants!
123:
"The design and materials chosen
showcase innovation. However, the
patchwork design lacks any central
theme."
125:
"We recommend focusing on
cultivating your own style."
133:
...Okay, there's no time to sit around
and pout! The judges and I just have
different tastes, that's all!
136:
Yeah! Next time, everyone's gonna
love what I come up with...
145:
This SUCKS! "Patchwork"? Are you
kidding me?!
148:
I worked so hard! Alk and Stella
helped out so much, too!
151:
We did everything right! I went out of
my way to imitate the popular
designs everyone likes, and didn't let
my own ideas get in the way!
154:
We didn't stand a chance to begin
with...
159:
I think second place is pretty great,
though.
162:
The comment was a little harsh, but
still. Second? The judges must have
liked it a lot to put you in second.
166:
B-but... I made it just like my mom
would... I imitated all sorts of
professionals!
171: Do you need to imitate others?
175:
W-well... I've gotta be just like my
mom, you know!
178:
...Nothing compares to what she
does... and I want to make
something uniquely my own, too...
184: ...Oh, sorry! I got carried away again...
190:
Don't worry, we get that you're
frustrated.
194:
Frustrated is right! I can hardly
stand it!
197:
That's why, next time, I'll design
something that only I can!
Everyone's going to love it, just you
wait!
205:
Wh-what's with the sudden change
in tone?!
208:
...But, yeah. I think I know what I have
to do now!
211:
Thanks so much for all your help,
you two!
216:
We're always here for you. I can't
wait to see what you make next.
220:
Maybe it's time we had dinner.
Whatever you choose to do, food's
always gotta be a priority.
225:
All right, then let me help you this
time! I can at least cut up the
veggies for you!
230:
Those scissors can cut vegetables,
too?!
235:
...Something only I can make, huh... A
design I'm passionate about.
237:
I wonder if Mom ever struggled with
stuff like this...
